1 Section 4041. A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury
2 a revolving fund to be designated as the "Oklahoma Route 66
3 Commission Revolving Fund", which shall consist of all monies
4 appropriated, transferred, or otherwise designated to the fund by
5 law. The revolving fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to
6 fiscal year limitations, and shall be under the administration of
7 the Oklahoma Route 66 Commission. All monies accruing to the credit
8 of said fund are hereby appropriated, and shall be budgeted and
9 expended in accordance with the provisions of subsection B of this
10 section for the purpose of preserving and developing Route 66 and
11 commemorating the Route 66 Centennial.
12 B. No funds Funds shall be budgeted or expended from the
13 Oklahoma Route 66 Commission Revolving Fund prior to July 1, 2023,
14 or prior to the approval by the Legislature of promulgated permanent
15 in accordance with rules adopted by the Commission pursuant to the
16 provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act.
17 C. The Oklahoma Route 66 Commission shall promulgate, pursuant
18 to the provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act, permanent
19 rules subject to approval by the Legislature, to implement:
20 1. Application procedures for projects submitting requests for
21 funds;
22 2. Processes for awarding of funding applications;
23 3. Details of the Commission's general duties;
